        "content": "<p>fitzgen edited <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13369\">PR #13369</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Introduce a new fuzz generator and oracle pair that gets/creates an object, accesses it, does a GC, and then asserts it still has the expected value. And it does that a few times inside loops and such in a way that if we mis-optimize (bad GVN/LICM) then we should trigger assertion failures.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 595401626,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778880606
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13369#pullrequestreview-4302060042\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 595417432,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778889230
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13369#discussion_r3251561498\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>When doing this, mind moving the default-enabling of v8 from the <code>wasmtime-fuzzing</code> crate to the <code>wasmtime-fuzz</code> harness at <code>fuzz/Cargo.toml</code>? Otherwise I think this change will turn off v8 fuzzing by default on oss-fuzz</p>\n</blockquote>",
